<div id="content">
<div id="blog-header"><h1><a href="/web/20100817183527/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/comments_blog/">Comments Blog</a></h1>
<h2>Because sometimes the comments <br>are the best part</h2></div>
	
	<!-- BLOG POSTS BEGIN HERE -->
	<!-- entries -->
	
	
	
	
		
		<div class="entry" id="entry-6a00d8341c630a53ef013486186759970c">
	
	<h1 class="entry-header"><a href="/web/20100817183527/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/comments_blog/2010/08/michelle-obamas-controversial-european-vacation.html" rel="bookmark" title="Michelle Obama's controversial European vacation">Michelle Obama's controversial European vacation</a></h1>
	
	
<div class="time" style="margin-bottom:8px;">August 10, 2010&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style="color:#8b0412;font-size:130%"> 7:08</span>
<span style="color:#8b0412">am</span></div>
	
	<div class="entry-content">
	<div class="entry-body clearfix">
	<a href="/web/20100817183527/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/.a/6a00d8341c630a53ef0133f2f50203970b-pi" style="display: inline;"><img alt="Spain&#39;s King Juan Carlos, right, welcomes U.S. first lady Michelle Obama and daughter Sasha, 9, on their arrival at the Marivent Palace, in Palma de Mallorca, Spain, Sunday, Aug. 8, 2010. The White House says first lady Michelle Obama is in Spain for a private trip with longtime family friends." class="asset asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c630a53ef0133f2f50203970b " src="/web/20100817183527im_/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/.a/6a00d8341c630a53ef0133f2f50203970b-600wi" style="width: 600px;" title="Spain&#39;s King Juan Carlos, right, welcomes U.S. first lady Michelle Obama and daughter Sasha, 9, on their arrival at the Marivent Palace, in Palma de Mallorca, Spain, Sunday, Aug. 8, 2010. The White House says first lady Michelle Obama is in Spain for a private trip with longtime family friends." /></a> <br /><p>What started out as a private vacation for a mother and daughter has developed into another friction point in a never-ending partisan brawl in politics.&#0160; </p>But that’s what happens when it’s the first lady. Michelle Obama’s recent trip to Spain stirred much criticism from commentators. The first lady stayed in Marbella with her youngest daughter and some friends at a hotel resort in the mountains.<br /><p>The Obamas paid for all personal expenses, but much criticism comes from the fact that the Secret Service personnel on the trip were funded by taxpayer dollars. Other criticism noted that the first lady chose to vacation in a foreign country rather than stay in the U.S. and spend her money at home.</p>Readers <a href="/web/20100817183527/http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-na-michelle-spain-20100807,0,4606035.story">expressed mixed reactions</a> to Michelle Obama’s getaway. Some agreed with the criticisms. Others defended the first lady and argued that her critics are out of line.<br />&#0160; <br /><blockquote>Beachgirl61: Please. All Michelle Obama has to do is wake in the morning and someone would criticize. Haters will always be haters. Stop trying to play her up as if she were some 21st Century Marie Antoinette.<br /><br />Hugenandi: Yet again, people get riled up because they forget that the President is not an average person. The tax payer costs come in because most people don&#39;t have to vacation with Secret Service or fly on ultra-secure state-owned jets.<br />Everything above the cost of first-class ticket and for the 1st Lady&#39;s hotel room is a cost of doing the job of President. Keep in mind that that ALL Presidents FOR LIFE have tax-payer funded Secret Service, etc. for EVERY DAY OF THEIR LIVES -- whether they are in Kansas or Antarctica.&#0160; It goes with the office of President and the tax payer costs last for decades!&#0160; <br /><br />skool411.info: White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs says Michelle Obama travels as a private citizen on a private trip ?!?! Excuse me but private citizen going on a private vacation does not take an entourage of U.S. secret service agents and other tax-funded helps *and* flying in Airforce 2. <br /><br />rafikiruby: People commented about the Clintons spending so much on Chelsea&#39;s wedding, but at least that money went to supporting American businesses and helping to keep Americans employed.&#0160; The fact she is lining the pockets of European businesses angers me to no end. She should be smart enough to know it just looks bad, especially when she just got done lecturing us about spending our vacations in the Gulf. I voted for Obama but this really rubs me the wrong way.<br /></blockquote>What’s your take? Was Michelle Obama in the wrong by visiting and supporting the economy of a foreign country? Or does she have a right to vacation wherever she wants?<br /><p>Share your thoughts in the comments below.</p><p>-- Ebony Bailey</p><p><em>Photo: Spain&#39;s King Juan Carlos, welcomes Michelle Obama and daughter Sasha, 9, on their arrival at the Marivent Palace, in Palma de Mallorca, Spain, on Sunday. Credit: Manu Mielniezuk / Associated Press<br /></em></p>
	</div>
	
	<!-- technorati tags -->
	


	
	</div>
	
	
