	<h1 class="entry-header"><a href="/web/20100817183527/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/comments_blog/2010/07/gun-control.html" rel="bookmark" title="Should you buy a gun? Readers take aim">Should you buy a gun? Readers take aim</a></h1>
	
	
<div class="time" style="margin-bottom:8px;">July 27, 2010&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style="color:#8b0412;font-size:130%">12:33</span>
<span style="color:#8b0412">pm</span></div>
	
	<div class="entry-content">
	<div class="entry-body clearfix">
	<p><img alt="Gun-woman" class="asset asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c630a53ef013485bf017b970c image-full " src="/web/20100817183527im_/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/.a/6a00d8341c630a53ef013485bf017b970c-pi" style="FLOAT: right; MARGIN: 0px 0px 5px 5px" title="Gun-woman" />Gun control, while a staple hot button issue, hasn&#39;t been discussed as frequently or pointedly recently as other subjects such as war, drugs or immigration.</p>
<p>Author <strong>Sonia Wolff</strong> contributed a guest opinion piece to the Sunday edition of The Times detailing her <a href="/web/20100817183527/http://www.latimes.com/news/opinion/commentary/la-oe-wolff-guns-20100725,0,3972515.story">domestic experiences with guns</a>. She reminisces about buying a handgun after being opposed to it and the accidental violence associated with it for some time.</p>
<p>Six dozen folks took shots at both sides of the 2nd Amendment issue.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Mar1n3r: The writer&#39;s take on gun ownership seems sound, and unless she or her husband develops dementia (they are old), she&#39;s unlikely to misuse her gun.</p>
<p>TomDavis: The theory that a woman lying dead in an alley is morally superior to a woman explaining to police how her attacker got shot.</p>
<p>Jcuenca: I remember watching &quot;world dumbest criminals&quot; and is true that the bad guys scatter like cockroaches at the sight of a gun. On the other hand (thankfully to some extent) most home burglaries are commited while the owners are away, and as I mentioned 500 000 guns are stolen every year in the US, so law-abiding citizens are de facto arming the criminals.</p></blockquote>
<p>Thoughts on gun control? Offload them in the comments.</p>
<p>-- Mark Milian<br /><span><a href="/web/20100817183527/http://twitter.com/markmilian">twitter.com/markmilian</a></span></p>
<p><em>Photo: KayCee Nelson, pictured July 8, is left-eye dominant but a right-handed shooter. When her parents, Ron and Tammy Nelson, finally heard their only child say, &quot;Get me a gun,&quot; they couldn&#39;t have been happier. Credit: Dennis Anderson / MCT</em></p>
	</div>
	
